      "tree": {
        "sha": "d03926ffd3bb5969fdd00de76efc2c85244399f4",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/d03926ffd3bb5969fdd00de76efc2c85244399f4"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree d03926ffd3bb5969fdd00de76efc2c85244399f4\nparent b110304705e1e1f97c88c4bb1455ab03c909450a\nauthor Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1777815407 +0200\ncommitter fanquake <fanquake@gmail.com> 1777989032 +0200\n\nci: unconfine seccomp for i686 no IPC\n\nDocker 29.4.2 blocks `socketcall(2)` in the default seccomp profile:\nhttps://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/29/#2942\nhttps://github.com/moby/profiles/releases/tag/seccomp%2Fv0.2.2\nhttps://github.com/moby/moby/pull/52501\n\nThat affects the `i686, no IPC` job because it runs 32-bit Linux test binaries inside Docker.\n\nAdd Docker's documented `--security-opt seccomp=unconfined` workaround to this job's `CI_CONTAINER_CAP` - the hook `ci/test/02_run_container.py` already appends to `docker run`.\n\nThis restores socket availability for the 32-bit test binaries throughout the job:\nhttps://docs.docker.com/engine/security/seccomp/#run-without-the-default-seccomp-profile\n\nGithub-Pull: #35202\nRebased-From: 11c9ef92a8daf030f75f88f324396b2248c65a64\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQJPBAABCAA5FiEEz7FuIclQ9n+pXlWPLuufXMCVJsEFAmn59akbFIAAAAAABAAO\nbWFudTIsMi41KzEuMTIsMCwzAAoJEC7rn1zAlSbB3SQP/1OR+Bk5MwOEtwSO3WOR\nfA0d/w/qg4zrkmJjwqg7rTAsIiY7W12gfdfWC013bK2qcKZT7JTko8Q4QjjfHbnD\nuebf7NeHR71khlJdGDasoWFga1MDgQK14laujV4SIaF79IYbIAxKZLeJkSVkZ9Sm\ntAVzhL7Tsnyyuh94NrFDLDv0Bb7NCVbywcw0wvCJeg4ToUlgJqtJwfZm3Y3NE09e\nO86qM4OdVqmzSilTDLTNVaHLWngKK4mxZFWf1IsQeBRj514W/kjZVsE7jxStNQM1\nOVldruhBCLkmg/KqJDfxaCaQbgq6yQrMHIWVj1IuHW+B5C+Nfct0KH1pmQGX5KYi\n10R+xwhdA5c5Z+B5DtwaxaY62yNalTI9/EYX3zhX1naGPUmJKGnDPm1mVj44H/Gm\nqrNFFIQzKInQnxrAUHd8NF5N/D/C8det5W6KSflDfbyd/57X+QLRou3ylGjAezS8\nJIQTvgejYBHxoZoa/YlsUKWMbOhNsQA6yRj2h7HyZyxzLNhHCxHWjB724Y9d1MnN\nSqv3E1pSk/UACOB+FVt0ftwGcaSdxUA31qq9cWu0AtNeVPZgvGfgJRfmT1ltvmSB\nvXYs+vqx6RvG0+HmrcHRcSXCRHXNl66/TRSM/guxdX00K8SC0F1V0iv70wDzDD5j\nh3aV2mErHYt0Go8G6OwTdyLt\n=vpeC\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
